Citation.sAbstract: The (p,q,T) of methanol, ethylbenzene and (methanol + benzene) and (methanol + ethylbenzene) at temperatures between (290 and 500) K and pressures in the range (0.1 to 60) MPa have been measured with a magnetic suspension densimeter with an uncertainty of +-0.1%. Our measurements with methanol deviate from the literature values by less than 0.2%. The (p,q,T) measurements were fitted with experimental uncertainties by an empirical equation. The temperature and mole fraction dependence of the coeffi-cients of the equation of state are presented.
